All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
CourseValidator
Validator overwrites isValid to validate that the given course input is 1 or more (inclusive) and less than 9.
DirectionButton
JButton that can also hold a directional value, and dynamically represents that directional value with an appropriate utf-8 arrow
EnergyValidator
Validator responsible for validating if a given user input can be evaluated as an int equal to or less then the specified max energy.
Enterprise
Representation of the Enterprise, handles internal state for the Enterprise in our game.
EnterpriseStatus
Takes the game state and represents the current state of the enterprise on the screen.
Entity
Entity is used to represent an Entity or 'thing' for want of a better term in the Game.
Faction
Enum for use indicating factional allegiance.
Galaxy
Handles the Quadrants held within the Galaxy.
Game
The main Game class responsible for holding all relevant classes for the game coordinating player and enemy actions.
GameController
Responsible for managing a JFrame that it manipulates as well as coordinating the interactions between the GameModel and the various Views.
GameLoader
GameLoader is responsible for well, loading the game state from a .trek file and building a new Enterprise and Galaxy.
GameModel
This is for specifying what methods are required specifically for use by the View, not every method in our Game that needs to be public for testing, needs to be exposed to our View.
GameSaver
A class responsible for saving the stringified game data to a .trek file.
GameView
This is for specifying what methods are required specifically for use by the View, not every method in our Game that needs to be public for testing, needs to be exposed to our View.
HasFaction
Indicates an Object implementing HasFaction can indicate that it belongs to a Faction and can indicate which one it belongs to.
HasPosition
Interface that indicates something has a position that can be viewed.
HasSymbol
Indicates the implementing Object has a String symbol representation that can be accessed.
Healable
Interface that indicates something is Healable via the heal() method.
Hittable
Interface that indicates something is Hittable for a given amount of damage.
ImageLoader
ImageLoader is responsible for loading a BufferedImage at given filepath.
ImageLoader
 
InputHandler
Responsible for handling user input, uses a given Validator to validate user input, and a given String for the user prompt to print.
Klingon
Klingon handles Entity behaviour plus some extra behaviour including: processing an attack, handling the details of being hit, managing its own energy reserve.
LoseGameView
A LoseGameView that shows the mission loss screen to the user, including an image loaded with ImageLoader.
Main
Main entry point for the program.
MapSquare
 
NearbyQuadrantScan
A view responsible for showing you the symbols of the surrounding quadrants.
Options
Presents a list of the main game options in a panel for the user.
Pallete
Enum for the colour pallete used throughout this project, intended to help remove magic hexcodes littering the codebase.
PhaserAttack
Displays the controls for choosing how much energy to allocate to a phaser attack using a Slider.
Positionable
Interface indicates the Object both has a viewable position (see HasPosition) and that position can be altered via these given interface methods.
Quadrant
Quadrant are sections of space with a randomised mixture of Stars, Klingons and Starbases.
QuadrantNavigation
Responsible for displaying an 8 button 'wheel' of DirectionButton for the 8 possible directions the Enterprise could be along and a Slider for how far to move it in that direction.
QuadrantScan
A view representing the internal state of the quadrant the player is in as a grid of squares, each indicating either empty, Klingon, Starbase, Star, Enterprise or unknown (i.e.
Shield
Displays the controls for choosing how much energy to re-allocate to shields using a Slider.
Slider
A JSlider that takes a given range of energy choices to represent.
StandardLayoutView
A standardised screen layout used for holding our various View, to hold 4 injected panels + a universal results panel above them that documents the results of the last game action.
Star
Star is a Entity that starts already scanned as it is pretty hard to not detect a Star in a Quadrant.
Starbase
Starbase is a Hittable Entity that can heal the Enterprise when it is adjacent to the Starbase in the same Quadrant.
StartView
A View configured for the starting screen view where it should have a JTextArea area holding the welcome message.
Stat
Stat wraps a numerical int value, with a minimum and maximum value enforced inclusively.
Torpedo
Shows controls for choosing the direction fire a torpedo using 8 DirectionButtons.
Validator
Validator passed to InputHandler for use in validating the users input.
View
A "view" is an extended JPanel that displays some information, presents some relevant ways to interact with it, it also handles tracking all the JButton assigned to it, their listeners and provides a way to clear them from memory when you wish to deconstruct the View.
WarpCoordValidator
Validator responsible for validating if the user String input can be evaluated as * conforming to either a NUMBER,NUMBER or NUMBER,NUMBER.NUMBER pattern.
WarpNavigation
Displays and handles the actions for managing warp based navigation, creating a Slider with a maximum value of 8 and minimum value of to control distance, surrounded by a ring of DirectionButtons one for each of the 8 possible directions that will allow us progress a game turn, move between quadrants in the game and then return to our default view.
WinGameView
A View that shows the mission success screen to the user.
XyPair
Represents a data object with an x and y Integer, used for things like position and vectors.
